	I have just uploaded version 1.00 of XDMD to the aminet.  It
should appear as util/rexx/xdmd1.lha.  XDMD stands for "XDME Macros by
Duniho."  It is the successor to DMD, which I last released a couple
years ago.  XDMD does for XDME what DMD did for DME, and it does a lot
more.  XDMD is an integrated system of macros, menus, keymappings,
ARexx scripts, and programs that together make XDME much more powerful
that it is by itself.  Its features include spell checking, outlining,
localized major modes, automatic mode selection upon loading, various
Emacs-like keymappings, region and rectangle editing a la Emacs, xpk
support, diary maintenance, pagination, many requesters, a "Windows"
menu that keeps track of each open file, and many other features.  I
hope that XDMD will give the authors of XDME a better feel for its
capabilities and limitations.  And I hope it will inspire further
development of XDME.

